'''Cristian Montano''' (born 11 December 1991) is a [[Football (soccer)|footballer]] who plays for [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]] on loan from [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]. He plays as a [[midfielder]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]]. He was born in [[Cali]], [[Columbia]]<ref name=Cali>{{cite web|title=MEET THE TEAMS WEST HAM UNITED|url=http://www.whufc.com/staticFiles/b/47/0,,12562~149259,00.pdf|publisher=www.whufc.com|accessdate=6 August 2011}}</ref> and moved to [[London]] as a child and holds nationality of both Columbia and the [[United Kingdom]].<ref name=U12>{{cite web|title=Cristian signs|url=http://www.whufc.com/articles/20100621/cristian-signs_2236884_2074131|publisher=www.whufc.com|accessdate=6 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Youth - 2009/10|url=http://www.whufc.com/articles/20100601/youths-200910-squad_2236884_1368925|publisher=www.whufc.com|accessdate=5 August 2011}}</ref> He has pledged any future international career to [[Colombia national football team|Columbia]] and models himself on [[Faustino Asprilla]].<ref name=Tino>{{cite news|last=Barlow|first=Matt|title=After Premier League 25-man squads announced, we introduce the top-flight kids from ... Fame!|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-130852 4/After-Premier-League-25-man-squads-announced-introduce-flight-kids---Fame.html|accessdate=6 August 2011|newspaper=www.dailymail.co.uk|date=11 September 2010}}</ref>

==Football career==
Montano joined West Ham as an under-12 player<ref name=U12/> signing his first professional contract in 2010. In August 2011 he signed a one-month loan deal with Notts County.<ref name=Nottsco1>{{cite web|title=Notts County sign West Ham forward Cristian Montano|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/14426609.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=5 August 2011}}</ref> Montano made his debut on 9 August 2011 in a [[Football League Cup|League Cup]] game against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] which Notts County lost on penalties after the game had finished 3-3.<ref name=Debut>{{cite web|title=Nott'm Forest   3 - 3   Notts County|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/league_cup/14368484.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=10 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Montano makes league bow|url=http://www.whufc.com/articles/20110809/montano-makes-league-bow_2236884_2415336|publisher=www.whufc.com|accessdate=10 August 2011}}</ref>

